      • Event

        public Event(java.lang.String message)
      throws javax.mail.MessagingException
        Constructor with email message.
        This message must be well formated and contains all neccessary parts (sender, receiver, date, subject and content), because it's used to extraction, so is necessary to have it.

        Example of well formated message:
        From: Filip Ogurcak <filip.ogurcak@gmail.com>
        To: filip.ogurcak@gmail.com
        Date: 1334571973
        Subject: aaa
        Content: The following is the information need for the arch set up. If you would like to volunteer to help fill out the attachment form* and drop by 1906

        Parameters:
        message - Represent the well formed headers and content of email message, from which could be extracted event data.
        Throws:
        javax.mail.MessagingException - when the message is badly formated

      • Event

        public Event(javax.mail.internet.MimeMessage message)
        Constructor with specific format of email message.
        This message contains all necessary parts (sender, receiver, date, subject and content), so it's easy to use it.

        Parameters:
        message - Represent the email message with all headers and content.
